l sector in the N</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">orth it is striking how diverse a range of companies there are – from games through to app developers</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> – but that they are fragmented and therefore, unlike TV and radio independents, are more difficult for the BBC to reach and work with.</span></li><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.11pt; padding-left:3.89pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">Initiatives such as the support given</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> by BBC North</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> to the Digital Fiction Factory </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">address this issue by developing a</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> net</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">work of digital companies</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> capable of meeting innovation briefs</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">.</span></li><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.11pt; padding-left:3.89pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">There </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">is </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">particular</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> problem </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">for</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> companies </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">based </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">in the North East</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> in terms of working with the BBC,</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> which could be addressed by targeted initiatives and a focus on communications with these co</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">mpanies.</span></li><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.73pt; padding-left:4.27pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Further initiatives to encourage greater collaboration with BBC North and BBC Online from northern digital agencies should be encouraged as these companies bring new approaches to reaching audiences – particularly younger </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">audiences – who the BBC w</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">ill need to reach in future if it is sustain its case for a universal licence fee.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">Philip </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">Reevell</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">Managing Director</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">December 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>